#. type: Title ^
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:646
#, no-wrap
msgid "bundle-uri CLIENT AND SERVER EXPECTATIONS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:648
#, no-wrap
msgid "URI CONTENTS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:650
msgid "The content at the advertised URIs MUST be one of two types."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:656
msgid ""
"The advertised URI may contain a bundle file that `git bundle verify` would "
"accept. I.e. they MUST contain one or more reference tips for use by the "
"client, MUST indicate prerequisites (in any) with standard \"-\" prefixes, "
"and MUST indicate their \"object-format\", if applicable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:661
msgid ""
"The advertised URI may alternatively contain a plaintext file that `git "
"config --list` would accept (with the `--file` option). The key-value pairs "
"in this list are in the `bundle.*` namespace (see linkgit:git-config[1])."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:662
#, no-wrap
msgid "bundle-uri CLIENT ERROR RECOVERY"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:667
msgid ""
"A client MUST above all gracefully degrade on errors, whether that error is "
"because of bad missing/data in the bundle URI(s), because that client is too "
"dumb to e.g. understand and fully parse out bundle headers and their "
"prerequisite relationships, or something else."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:674
msgid ""
"Server operators should feel confident in turning on \"bundle-uri\" and not "
"worry if e.g. their CDN goes down that clones or fetches will run into hard "
"failures. Even if the server bundle(s) are incomplete, or bad in some way "
"the client should still end up with a functioning repository, just as if it "
"had chosen not to use this protocol extension."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:677
msgid ""
"All subsequent discussion on client and server interaction MUST keep this in "
"mind."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:678
#, no-wrap
msgid "bundle-uri SERVER TO CLIENT"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:683
msgid ""
"The ordering of the returned bundle uris is not significant. Clients MUST "
"parse their headers to discover their contained OIDS and prerequisites. A "
"client MUST consider the content of the bundle(s)  themselves and their "
"header as the ultimate source of truth."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:688
msgid ""
"A server MAY even return bundle(s) that don't have any direct relationship "
"to the repository being cloned (either through accident, or intentional "
"\"clever\" configuration), and expect a client to sort out what data they'd "
"like from the bundle(s), if any."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:689
#, no-wrap
msgid "bundle-uri CLIENT TO SERVER"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:695
msgid ""
"The client SHOULD provide reference tips found in the bundle header(s)  as "
"'have' lines in any subsequent `fetch` request. A client MAY also ignore the "
"bundle(s) entirely if doing so is deemed worse for some reason, e.g. if the "
"bundles can't be downloaded, it doesn't like the tips it finds etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:696
#, no-wrap
msgid "WHEN ADVERTISED BUNDLE(S) REQUIRE NO FURTHER NEGOTIATION"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:702
msgid ""
"If after issuing `bundle-uri` and `ls-refs`, and getting the header(s)  of "
"the bundle(s) the client finds that the ref tips it wants can be retrieved "
"entirely from advertised bundle(s), the client MAY disconnect from the Git "
"server. The results of such a 'clone' or 'fetch' should be indistinguishable "
"from the state attained without using bundle-uri."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:703
#, no-wrap
msgid "EARLY CLIENT DISCONNECTIONS AND ERROR RECOVERY"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:708
msgid ""
"A client MAY perform an early disconnect while still downloading the "
"bundle(s) (having streamed and parsed their headers). In such a case the "
"client MUST gracefully recover from any errors related to finishing the "
"download and validation of the bundle(s)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:711
msgid ""
"I.e. a client might need to re-connect and issue a 'fetch' command, and "
"possibly fall back to not making use of 'bundle-uri' at all."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:719
msgid ""
"This \"MAY\" behavior is specified as such (and not a \"SHOULD\") on the "
"assumption that a server advertising bundle uris is more likely than not to "
"be serving up a relatively large repository, and to be pointing to URIs that "
"have a good chance of being in working order. A client MAY e.g. look at the "
"payload size of the bundles as a heuristic to see if an early disconnect is "
"worth it, should falling back on a full \"fetch\" dialog be necessary."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:720
#, no-wrap
msgid "WHEN ADVERTISED BUNDLE(S) REQUIRE FURTHER NEGOTIATION"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:724
msgid ""
"A client SHOULD commence a negotiation of a PACK from the server via the "
"\"fetch\" command using the OID tips found in advertised bundles, even if's "
"still in the process of downloading those bundle(s)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:732
msgid ""
"This allows for aggressive early disconnects from any interactive server "
"dialog. The client blindly trusts that the advertised OID tips are relevant, "
"and issues them as 'have' lines, it then requests any tips it would like "
"(usually from the \"ls-refs\" advertisement) via 'want' lines. The server "
"will then compute a (hopefully small) PACK with the expected difference "
"between the tips from the bundle(s) and the data requested."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:738
msgid ""
"The only connection the client then needs to keep active is to the "
"concurrently downloading static bundle(s), when those and the incremental "
"PACK are retrieved they should be inflated and validated. Any errors at this "
"point should be gracefully recovered from, see above."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ^
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:740
#, no-wrap
msgid "bundle-uri PROTOCOL FEATURES"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:747
msgid ""
"The client constructs a bundle list from the `<key>=<value>` pairs provided "
"by the server. These pairs are part of the `bundle.*` namespace as "
"documented in linkgit:git-config[1]. In this section, we discuss some of "
"these keys and describe the actions the client will do in response to this "
"information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:751
msgid ""
"In particular, the `bundle.version` key specifies an integer value. The only "
"accepted value at the moment is `1`, but if the client sees an unexpected "
"value here then the client MUST ignore the bundle list."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:756
msgid ""
"As long as `bundle.version` is understood, all other unknown keys MAY be "
"ignored by the client. The server will guarantee compatibility with older "
"clients, though newer clients may be better able to use the extra keys to "
"minimize downloads."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:761
msgid ""
"Any backwards-incompatible addition of pre-URI key-value will be guarded by "
"a new `bundle.version` value or values in 'bundle-uri' capability "
"advertisement itself, and/or by new future `bundle-uri` request arguments."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:764
msgid ""
"Some example key-value pairs that are not currently implemented but could be "
"implemented in the future include:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:767
msgid ""
"Add a \"hash=<val>\" or \"size=<bytes>\" advertise the expected hash or size "
"of the bundle file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:770
msgid ""
"Advertise that one or more bundle files are the same (to e.g. have clients "
"round-robin or otherwise choose one of N possible files)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:774
msgid ""
"A \"oid=<OID>\" shortcut and \"prerequisite=<OID>\" shortcut. For expressing "
"the common case of a bundle with one tip and no prerequisites, or one tip "
"and one prerequisite."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:778
msgid ""
"This would allow for optimizing the common case of servers who'd like to "
"provide one \"big bundle\" containing only their \"main\" branch, and/or "
"incremental updates thereof."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation-sedout/gitprotocol-v2.txt:783
msgid ""
"A client receiving such a a response MAY assume that they can skip "
"retrieving the header from a bundle at the indicated URI, and thus save "
"themselves and the server(s) the request(s) needed to inspect the headers of "
"that bundle or bundles."
msgstr ""

